Definition: in probate law: the legal right of a surviving spouse to elect to take either what the deceased spouse gave under the will or the share of the estate as set forth by statute
Synonyms: legal_right, noun, group, law, c, in, probate, the, legal, right, of, a, surviving, spouse, to, elect, take, either, what, deceased, gave, under, will, or, share, estate, as, set, forth, by, statute
Category: noun.attribute
